how to run file...

1. copy calc.l and input.txt files into some folder

2. open terminal(shell)  to compile and execute the program

3. reach up the path where you have copy the file

4. compile lex program calc.l by giving "lex calc.l"

5. after successful compilition it must create lex.yy.c in to same directory

6. now compile .c program by "gcc lex.yy.c -ll"

7. after successful compilation its must create a.out in to same directory
 
8. to execute the program type ./a.out < input.txt

9. program will fatch the content of the input file and will show the output based on fatched content.

10. if you want to taste the output for other than given streams you can edit the input.txt file.
